{"id": "EUVD-2020-6462", "enisaUuid": "d706bdfc-7cfc-3456-9347-d4060a859ece", "description": "There is an issue on grub2 before version 2.06 at function read_section_as_string(). It expects a font name to be at max UINT32_MAX - 1 length in bytes but it doesn't verify it before proceed with buffer allocation to read the value from the font value. An attacker may leverage that by crafting a malicious font file which has a name with UINT32_MAX, leading to read_section_as_string() to an arithmetic overflow, zero-sized allocation and further heap-based buffer overflow.", "datePublished": "2020-07-31T20:55:55", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-04T12:39:36", "baseScore": 5.7, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2020-14310.html", "https://www.debian.org/security/2020/dsa-4735", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3276", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3275", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3274", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3273", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3271", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3227", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3223", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3217", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3216", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2020-14310", "https://advisories.mageia.org/CVE-2020-14310.html", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2020-14310.html", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=CVE-2020-14310", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/4432-1/", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2020-08/msg00017.html", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2020-08/msg00016.html", "https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/202104-05"], "aliases": ["CVE-2020-14310"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "d5a9942d-abf1-34dd-8a29-ba2440229d9f", "product": {"name": "grub2"}, "product_version": "2.06"}], "enisaIdVendor"